The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Villa certain they have Heskey
                                                   In amp; Out
                      
	Villa certain they have Heskey  
	Aston Villa manager Martin Neill believes he has won the battle to sign Wigan striker Emile Heskey and expects to seal a 3m move on Friday.   
	City offer for Drogba         
	Manchester City have offered striker Didier Drogba a double-your-money deal worth 180,000 a week to quit Chelsea. City are also ready to pay 19m for Sporting Lisbon and Portugal midfielder Miguel Veloso. Meanwhile, Chelsea defender Branislav Ivanovic, 24, will snub Manchester City for a move to Serie A club Fiorentina.         
	West Ham close in on Nsereko         
	West Ham United are close to agreeing a deal to sign Brescias Savio Nsereko for a fee that could total 10 million after club executives spent the last two days in Italy holding talks. West Ham have been told they will have to double their 4m offer for Cardiff and Wales winger Joe Ledley.         
	Spurs interested in Cole         
	Tottenham Hotspur are ready to revive their interest in West Hams Carlton Cole after they had a 8 million bid for the striker turned down in the beginning of January.         
	Bullard joins Hull         
	Hull City broke their transfer record to sign central midfielder Jimmy Bullard from Premier League rivals Fulham on Friday.         
	Bullard joined for a fee of 5 million ($6.89 million), the northern club said on their website.         
	Juventus eye Kuyt         
	Juventus have reportedly stepped up their interest in Liverpools Dirk Kuyt as coach Claudio Ranieri tries to find a replacement for midfielder Pavel Nedved. Chelseas French striker Florent Malouda too is being considered by Juventus for filling the Nedved void.         
	Blackburn to bid for Janko         
	Blackburn Rovers manager Sam Allardyce is ready to make a 6m bid for Red Bull Salzburg striker Marc Janko.   
